{"art": [{"brightcove": "", "caption": "Citizen Action of Wisconsin says U.S. Sen. Ron Johnson, R-Wis., cracks down on dissenters and posted this letter as evidence. ", "id": 10551, "infogram": "", "ndn": "", "ndnid": "", "other": "", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/photos/Cease_desist_letter.png", "resource_type": {"id": 1, "name": "Photo", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/mediatype/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/media/10551/", "title": "Cease desist letter", "wibbitz": "", "youtube": "", "youtubeID": ""}], "author": [{"email_address": "tkertscher@journalsentinel.com", "first_name": "Tom", "id": 171, "last_name": "Kertscher", "name_slug": "tom-kertscher", "on_staff_page": 94, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 10, "publication_name": "Milwaukee Journal Sentinel", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/10/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/171/", "title": "PolitiFact Wisconsin writer", "twitter": ""}], "canonical_url": "/wisconsin/statements/2017/mar/07/resistance-report/article-falsely-claims-ron-johnson-threatens-citiz/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Wisconsin", "edition": "Wisconsin", "edition_slug": "wisconsin", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 8, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The Wisconsin Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/8/"}, "editor": [{"email_address": "gborowski@journalsentinel.com", "first_name": "Greg", "id": 170, "last_name": "Borowski", "name_slug": "greg-borowski", "on_staff_page": null, "phone": null, "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 10, "publication_name": "Milwaukee Journal Sentinel", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/10/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/170/", "title": "PolitiFact Wisconsin editor", "twitter": null}], "facebook_headline": "Ron Johnson threatens jail for citizens seeking town hall?", "id": 13824, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": false, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "tkertscher@journalsentinel.com", "first_name": "Tom", "id": 171, "last_name": "Kertscher", "name_slug": "tom-kertscher", "on_staff_page": 94, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 10, "publication_name": "Milwaukee Journal Sentinel", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/10/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/171/", "title": "PolitiFact Wisconsin writer", "twitter": ""}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/13824/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "Pants on Fire", "id": 6, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/6/", "ruling": "Pants on Fire!", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-pantsonfire.gif", "ruling_slug": "pants-fire"}, "ruling_comments": "<p>Some Facebook readers flagged as &quot;fake news&quot; a March 2, 2017 <a href=\"http://resistancereport.com/politics/senator-citizen-arrest-town-hall/\">article</a> that carried this headline about Wisconsin&rsquo;s Ron Johnson:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Republican Senator Threatens Citizens with Arrest if They Continue Asking for a Town Hall</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The article was published by Resistance Report, which <a href=\"http://resistancereport.com/about/\">describes itself</a> as a &quot;social justice-oriented media company dedicated to providing the bold, combative, thought-provoking journalism that will be critical over the next four years.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, we thought we&rsquo;d see whether Johnson made such a threat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A letter</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The article accuses Johnson of dodging requests to hold town hall meetings, but eventually responding to the requests with a &quot;cease-and-desist&quot; letter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But that letter had nothing to do with town hall meetings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#\">As we </a><a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/wisconsin/statements/2017/mar/02/citizen-action-wisconsin/group-falsely-claims-gop-sen-ron-johnson-sends-cea/\">reported</a> on the same day the Resistance Report article was published, Johnson had sent a letter to a Milwaukee man who acknowledged he had called Johnson&rsquo;s office as many as 83 times in a day. The letter warned that if the man visited or called Johnson&rsquo;s office (written communication was OK), staff would call U.S. Capitol Police.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Citizen Action of Wisconsin had cited the letter in claiming that &quot;people who come to&quot; their dissent actions &quot;get a &lsquo;cease and desist&rsquo; letter&quot; from Johnson&#39;s office. We <a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/wisconsin/statements/2017/mar/02/citizen-action-wisconsin/group-falsely-claims-gop-sen-ron-johnson-sends-cea/\">rated the group&rsquo;s claim False</a>. The man was involved in some Citizen Action activities involving Johnson. But the letter was based on his personal contact with Johnson&rsquo;s office, not any Citizen Action activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(A few days later, Citizen Action <a href=\"http://www.citizenactionwi.org/setting_the_record_straight_on_the_ron_johnson_cease_and_desist_letter?hootPostID=81393aeb2f137ae7cd05e801810748b4\">posted an apology</a> for making its claim.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tom Cahill, an editor for Resistance Report, told us that since the man &quot;had called his senator&#39;s office 83 times, it seems as if his goal is for Johnson to hold a public town hall so his senator can answer his questions directly.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But that is complete speculation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The letter also went to a single person. It was not a general response to &quot;citizens&quot; who may request a town hall meeting, as the article claimed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Our rating</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Resistance Report says Johnson &quot;threatens citizens with arrest if they continue asking for a town hall.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A letter by Johnson&rsquo;s office that was cited by the group warned a man that if he did not stop calling and visiting Johnson&rsquo;s office, the Capitol Police would be called. The letter had nothing to do with town hall meetings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We rate the statement Pants on Fire.</p> <div class=\"sharethefacts_microdata_embed\" data-sharethefacts-uuid=\"93929ce1-ad9c-4185-a11a-2d942b69770c\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 200px; padding: 10px 10px 30px 10px; margin-bottom: 50px; color: gray; font-style: italic; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ClaimReview\"> <div style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Share the Facts</div> <div style=\"width: auto; margin: 20px 25px 20px 25px\"> <div style=\"display: none;\" itemprop=\"author\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Organization\"> <div itemprop=\"name\"><a itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://www.politifact.com\">Politifact</a></div> <img itemprop=\"image\" src=\"http://static.politifact.com/mediapage/jpgs/politifact-logo-big.jpg\" alt=\"Politifact\" /> </div> <div style=\"font-size: 14px; margin: 0px, 0px, 0px, 0px\" itemprop=\"reviewRating\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Rating\"> <div style=\"display: none;\" itemprop=\"ratingValue\">6</div> <div style=\"display: none;\" itemprop=\"bestRating\">7</div> <img style=\"display: none;\" itemprop=\"image\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/share-the-facts/rating_images/politifact/tom-pof.png\" alt=\"Politifact rating logo\" /> Politifact Rating: <div style=\"font-weight: bold\" itemprop=\"alternateName\">Pants on Fire</div> </div> <div style=\"margin: 20px 0px 10px 0px\" itemprop=\"claimReviewed\">Says U.S. Sen. Ron Johnson \"threatens citizens with arrest if they continue asking for a town hall.\"</div> <div style=\"font-size: 12px; margin: 10px 10px 20px 150px\"> <div itemprop=\"itemReviewed\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/CreativeWork\"> <div itemprop=\"author\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\"> <div itemprop=\"name\">Resistance Report</div> <div itemprop=\"jobTitle\">Organization</div> </div> <img style=\"display:none;\" itemprop=\"image\" src=\"http://static.politifact.com.s3.amazonaws.com/politifact/mugs/mugs_mug-independentgroup__________________.jpg\" /> <div style=\"margin: 5px 0px 0px 14px\" itemprop=\"name\">In an article</div> <div style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 14px\">Thursday, March 2, 2017</div> <div style=\"display: none;\" itemprop=\"datePublished\">03/02/2017</div> </div> </div> <div style=\"font-size: 12px; margin: 5px 0px 0px 0px; width: 400px;\"> <a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/wisconsin/statements/2017/mar/07/resistance-report/article-falsely-claims-ron-johnson-threatens-citiz/\" itemprop=\"url\">Read More</a> <div style=\"float: right\"> <a href=\"#\">info</a> </div> </div> </div> </div>\r\n", "ruling_comments_date": "2017-03-07T11:11:44.111213", "ruling_date": "2017-03-07T11:47:17", "ruling_headline": "Article falsely claims that Ron Johnson threatens citizens with arrest over town hall meetings", "ruling_headline_slug": "article-falsely-claims-ron-johnson-threatens-citiz", "ruling_link_text": "No such threat", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p>Resistance Report, <a href=\"http://resistancereport.com/politics/senator-citizen-arrest-town-hall/\">&quot;Republican Senator Threatens Citizens with Arrest if They Continue Asking for a Town Hall,&quot;</a> March 2, 2017</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Email, Resistance Report editor <a href=\"http://resistancereport.com/about/\">Tom Cahill</a>, March 6, 2017</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PolitiFact Wisconsin, <a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/wisconsin/statements/2017/mar/02/citizen-action-wisconsin/group-falsely-claims-gop-sen-ron-johnson-sends-cea/\">&quot;Group falsely claims that GOP Sen. Ron Johnson sends &#39;cease-and-desist&#39; letters to activists,&quot;</a> March 2, 2017</p>\r\n", "speaker": {"adkey": null, "advalue": null, "barely_true_count": 0, "current_job": "", "false_count": 0, "first_name": "", "half_true_count": 0, "home_state": "", "id": 3856, "last_name": "Resistance Report", "mostly_true_count": 0, "name_slug": "resistance-report", "pants_count": 1, "party": {"id": 1